#  Image Editor

A simple image editor built with **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**. It lets you upload an image, adjust filters in real time, apply presets, and download the edited image directly from your browser.

## Features

* Upload images from your device
* Adjust filters with sliders

  * Brightness
  * Contrast
  * Saturation
  * Hue Rotation
  * Blur
  * Grayscale
  * Sepia
  * Opacity
  * Invert
* Apply built-in filter presets
* Reset all filters with one click
* Download the edited image
* Clean and responsive interface

## Tech Stack

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* HTML5 Canvas API

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/image-editor.git
```

2. Open the project folder.

3. Open `index.html` in your browser.

That's it—no installation or dependencies are required.

## Project Structure

```text
image-editor/
├── index.html
├── style.css
├── theme.css
├── script.js
└── README.md
```

